1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
Matthew, Matthew chapter number 6.

2
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:06,000
And in just a very few moments, I'm going to begin reading

3
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:09,000
in verse number 19 of the chapter

4
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:12,000
and be reading through verse number 21.

5
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:15,000
We will be using our Bibles again tonight

6
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:18,000
and therefore I trust you'll leave them handy

7
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:21,000
throughout the course of the message.

8
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:24,000
My, hasn't the service been a blessing thus far?

9
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:27,000
I've enjoyed every part of the service,

10
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:31,000
the congregational singing has just been wonderful.

11
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:34,000
The children singing tonight was outstanding.

12
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:37,000
And then to be able to see firsthand

13
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:40,000
how God used Brother Tim there in Bulgaria.

14
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:44,000
And I know that thrills you as a sending church family

15
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:48,000
to have a part in what the Lord used him to do there.

16
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:51,000
And so it was a blessing to hear from him.

17
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:54,000
And what a blessing this week has been.

18
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:58,000
And it just seems like we've just really gotten started

19
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:00,000
and here it is Wednesday night.

20
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:03,000
And Cassie and I will be on the road early tomorrow morning

21
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:06,000
headed at least toward home.

22
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:08,000
And we certainly appreciate your prayers.

23
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:12,000
But as we leave, we're certainly going to be leaving blessed.

24
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:16,000
It has been a great few days here at the Fellowship Baptist Church.

25
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:20,000
Your pastor and your pastor's wife and their family

26
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:23,000
have been outstanding and very gracious hosts

27
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:26,000
to all of our missionary families here this week.

28
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:29,000
And we from the bottom of our hearts say,

29
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:31,000
thank you, thank you, thank you.

30
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:34,000
Let me say again that the Fellowship Baptist Church,

31
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:36,000
thank you so much for your prayerful

32
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:39,000
as well as your financial support.

33
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:43,000
We could not do what God has put in our hearts to do

34
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:46,000
without pastors like your precious pastor

35
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:49,000
and without churches just like the Fellowship Baptist Church.

36
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:52,000
And Cassie and I are blessed to be your representatives

37
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:54,000
literally all over the world.

38
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:58,000
Lord willing, next month we'll be in Brazil

39
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:00,000
and we appreciate your help to get there.

40
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:02,000
You've just been so good to us.

41
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:04,000
We're very, very grateful.

42
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:08,000
And we're already looking forward to the next time.

43
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:12,000
We've already got a date scheduled in 2028.

44
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:14,000
We're excited about that.

45
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:16,000
Now, if Jesus comes before then,

46
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:19,000
Brother Bill will be in charge of the services.

47
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:21,000
So you folks that are left,

48
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:24,000
maybe he can give you something from the Bible.

49
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:27,000
But I want to say it's so good to see my dear friend,

50
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:29,000
Brother Alton Bill, here tonight.

51
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:32,000
And all of these folks from Ambassador,

52
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:35,000
it's amazing to watch the Lord use them

53
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:37,000
during the D.C. outreach.

54
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:40,000
And we're just so thrilled about that.

55
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:42,000
I'm so appreciative for the burden

56
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:45,000
that God put on Brother Bill's heart about that.

57
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:49,000
Surely our nation needs the gospel.

58
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:53,000
And what better time to try to reach D.C. with the gospel

59
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:56,000
than during this 250-year celebration

60
00:02:56,000 --> 00:03:01,000
when literally thousands upon thousands of people will be here.

61
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:04,000
So I'm so appreciative for your burden, Brother Bill.

62
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:06,000
And I'll tell you, I'm impressed.

63
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:09,000
I'm always impressed with the Ambassador guys.

64
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:11,000
They're just always a step above.

65
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:15,000
And I love Ambassador Baptist College and Brother Alton Bill.

66
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:20,000
It's a blessing to call him one of my friends.

67
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:22,000
And to get to meet these other fellas,

68
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:24,000
the fella from Brother Nate.

69
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:27,000
It's the first time I've met Brother Nate.

70
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:31,000
And from West Virginia, then Brother Ryan DeLay.

71
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:33,000
It's just been a great, great blessing.

72
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:36,000
And all of the missionary families this week,

73
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:38,000
it's just been very refreshing.

74
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:42,000
I so appreciate the message from Brother Perez last night.

75
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:45,000
And it's a blessing to hear a missionary preach

76
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:51,000
with tears in his eyes and with a flame of fire in his heart.

77
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:55,000
And that's exactly how Brother Perez preached last night.

78
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:57,000
And I'm so appreciative.

79
00:03:57,000 --> 00:04:01,000
Have you found your place in the gospel of Matthew chapter number 6?

80
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:05,000
I felt impressed of the Lord tonight to challenge you

81
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:07,000
about your missions giving.

82
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:10,000
And on the way to the pulpit this evening,

83
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:15,000
I was careful to pick up one of your giving envelopes.

84
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:20,000
Now your pastor makes these available to you every single week

85
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:22,000
here at the Fellowship Baptist Church.

86
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:25,000
And of course, first and foremost,

87
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:29,000
there's a place right here for you to tithe every week.

88
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:32,000
And we know when we study our Bible,

89
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:35,000
giving begins with the tithe.

90
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:37,000
The tithe belongs to the Lord.

91
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:41,000
But then there is a place for you every single week,

92
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:43,000
right along with your tithes and offerings,

93
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:47,000
there's a place on your giving envelopes for you to pray

94
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:51,000
about a very special gift or an investment,

95
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:55,000
as we will call it tonight, in world evangelism.

96
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:59,000
And of course, that is to be given over and above the tithe.

97
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:03,000
So I'm thankful your pastor has given you an opportunity

98
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:07,000
through the ministry of Fellowship Baptist Church

99
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:13,000
for you to make an investment in world evangelism.

100
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:17,000
It is an investment, as we will see tonight,

101
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:22,000
in which you or I, either one, cannot lose.

102
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:23,000
Amen?

103
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:25,000
With that in mind, would you stand if you're able

104
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:28,000
as I read just three verses of Scripture

105
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:32,000
in the sixth chapter of the Gospel of Matthew

106
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:34,000
beginning with verse 19.

107
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:37,000
We'll read the text and then consider the context

108
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:40,000
of its writing throughout the introduction

109
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:43,000
of the Bible message tonight.

110
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:46,000
Matthew chapter 6 and verse 19.

111
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:47,000
The Lord says,

112
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:51,000
Lay not up for yourselves treasures upon earth,

113
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:55,000
where moth and rust doth corrupt,

114
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:59,000
and where thieves break through and steal.

115
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:03,000
But lay up for yourselves treasures in heaven,

116
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:07,000
where neither moth nor rust doth corrupt,

117
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:11,000
and where thieves do not break through nor steal.

118
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:15,000
For where your treasure is,

119
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:20,000
there will your heart be also.

120
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:24,000
I would like to back up and read verse 21 again

121
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:26,000
and encourage each and every one of you,

122
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:27,000
if you would please,

123
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:31,000
to read this verse of Scripture audibly with me.

124
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:33,000
Would you read it with me this evening?

125
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:35,000
Let's read verse 21 together.

126
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:39,000
For where your treasure is,

127
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:42,000
there will your heart be also.

128
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:44,000
With the help of the Lord tonight,

129
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:46,000
I want to preach on this thought,

130
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:52,000
truths concerning our treasures.

131
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:56,000
I believe the Lord Jesus shares such truths with us

132
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:59,000
here in these few verses of Scripture

133
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:02,000
that He's led us to tonight.

134
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:08,000
I like to call them truths concerning our treasures.

135
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:11,000
Let's see what Jesus has to say

136
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:15,000
about a few of those truths tonight.

137
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:17,000
Let's bow our heads for a moment of prayer.

138
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:21,000
Father, it has certainly been memorable,

139
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:22,000
to say the least,

140
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:26,000
last few days here at the Fellowship Baptist Church.

141
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:28,000
I want to thank you for Pastor Man and his family

142
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:30,000
and their leadership here

143
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:34,000
and how that you continue to use them in a mighty way.

144
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:37,000
And then, Lord, I want to thank you for a church family

145
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:40,000
that's willing to follow His faith.

146
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:42,000
And I pray, my Father,

147
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:45,000
that the greatest days of outreach

148
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:47,000
for the Fellowship Baptist Church

149
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:52,000
will still be yet to come in the days ahead.

150
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:54,000
And for that, I'll give you glory and honor.

151
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:57,000
Now, Father, would you please help me tonight?

152
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:59,000
I'm nothing without you.

153
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:02,000
So I pray you'd cleanse me of sin and self

154
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:04,000
and fill me with your Holy Spirit.

155
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:09,000
If you would be so kind as to make a preacher out of me tonight,

156
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:11,000
I certainly would appreciate it.

157
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:14,000
In Jesus' name I pray, amen.

158
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:16,000
Thank you so much for standing.

159
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:17,000
Please be seated.

160
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:20,000
As you and I consider the context of the verses

161
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:23,000
we've just been blessed to read together,

162
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:25,000
we'll discover they're actually a part

163
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:28,000
of what some Bible commentators have called

164
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:33,000
the very heart of our Lord's Sermon on the Mount.

165
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:35,000
During the course of that sermon,

166
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:40,000
the Lord Jesus, He addresses not merely outward conduct,

167
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:43,000
but rather inward priorities.

168
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:46,000
Here in the text that He's led us to tonight,

169
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:48,000
He's addressing truths.

170
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:53,000
Again, I like to call them truths concerning our treasures.

171
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:56,000
And while sharing those truths with us,

172
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:58,000
it's very interesting this evening.

173
00:08:58,000 --> 00:09:04,000
Jesus isn't concerned with telling us what we want to hear.

174
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:05,000
Oh, no, no.

175
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:09,000
He's telling us in the text what we need to hear.

176
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:11,000
And friend, if there's ever been a day,

177
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:13,000
if there's ever been an hour,

178
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:15,000
that the world needs to hear

179
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:18,000
what our Lord is saying here in the text,

180
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:22,000
it's in this day and hour in which we're living today.

181
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:27,000
I say that because in a world that is driven by accumulation,

182
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:31,000
investment portfolios, and material security,

183
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:33,000
here in the text before us,

184
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:38,000
our Lord speaks plainly, and I believe very pointedly,

185
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:43,000
about what truly matters, about what truly lasts.

186
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:46,000
And His concern, according to the text,

187
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:51,000
isn't whether or not we possess earthly goods,

188
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:56,000
but rather whether or not earthly goods possess us.

189
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:59,000
Now, please, let me make it very clear.

190
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:02,000
beginning of the message this evening.

191
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:05,000
There's nothing wrong with having things.

192
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:08,000
There's nothing wrong with having earthly goods.

193
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:10,000
But the Bible is abundantly clear.

194
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:16,000
It becomes a sin when things or earthly goods have us.

195
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:20,000
I want to say tonight there's nothing wrong with having money.

196
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:24,000
Having been in the ministry now for over three decades,

197
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:26,000
I'm thankful for those that have money.

198
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:28,000
There's nothing wrong with having money.

199
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:32,000
And by the way, do you know what it takes to reach the world with the gospel?

200
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:37,000
Now you can dismiss this truth all you would like, but it takes money.

201
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:43,000
Do you know what it takes to plant a church in Uruguay or Bulgaria?

202
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:45,000
I'm telling you, it takes a lot of money.

203
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:51,000
Do you know what it takes to reach D.C. with the gospel of the Lord Jesus Christ?

204
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:55,000
You can dismiss it any way you want to dismiss it,

205
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:58,000
but you can't deny it takes money to do it.

206
00:10:58,000 --> 00:11:01,000
There's nothing wrong with money.

207
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:05,000
The Bible doesn't say that money is the root of all evil.

208
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:10,000
The Bible says in 1 Timothy chapter 6 and verse number 10

209
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:15,000
that the love of money is the root of all evil.

210
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:19,000
That's why these verses of scripture are so vitally important

211
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:22,000
for the Fellowship Baptist Church this evening,

212
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:27,000
especially as you seek God's perfect will

213
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:32,000
about your investment in world evangelism in the days to come.

214
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:36,000
These verses of scripture are vitally important

215
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:38,000
because here in the text before us,

216
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:44,000
the Lord can actually be seen contrasting two treasuries.

217
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:46,000
Two treasuries.

218
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:48,000
One treasury is temporal.

219
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:50,000
It is fragile.

220
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:52,000
But according to these verses of scripture,

221
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:55,000
the other treasury is eternal.

222
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:57,000
It is secure.

223
00:11:57,000 --> 00:12:01,000
And then as the Lord so often does in his word,

224
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:05,000
in light of truths concerning those two treasuries,

225
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:10,000
he calls upon you and he ultimately calls upon me

226
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:15,000
to choose between them very wisely.

227
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:17,000
This last night of your missions conference,

228
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:21,000
I implore you, church, in light of eternity,

229
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:25,000
please choose wisely.

230
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:28,000
And as you and I contemplate our choices,

231
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:33,000
please allow me to remind you that world evangelism

232
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:37,000
is at its very core an investment question.

233
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:42,000
World evangelism causes us to ask ourselves,

234
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:46,000
where are we placing the resources

235
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:50,000
that God has entrusted us with?

236
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:54,000
I think it's important that you hear the preacher say tonight,

237
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:59,000
I don't think there's a thing in this world wrong with saving.

238
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:02,000
I don't think there's a thing wrong with investing.

239
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:05,000
In fact, I try to do a little bit of that myself.

240
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:08,000
Proverbs chapter six and verse number six says,

241
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:13,000
go to the aunt thou sluggard, consider her ways and be wise.

242
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:15,000
I would encourage you to save.

243
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:19,000
I would encourage you to invest and plan wisely.

244
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:21,000
However, in light of that,

245
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:24,000
I want you to listen to what I'm getting ready to say.

246
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:28,000
I would hate to think that I would have more invested

247
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:31,000
in this temporary world below

248
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:36,000
than I had invested in the eternal world in heaven to come.

249
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:38,000
So with that truth in mind,

250
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:41,000
there is a question that both you and I

251
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:44,000
ought to earnestly consider this evening.

252
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:49,000
Are we living only for what can be seen, counted, and consumed?

253
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:54,000
Or are we intentionally laying up treasures

254
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:58,000
where moth, rust, and thieves have no access?

255
00:13:58,000 --> 00:14:00,000
Please hear me tonight.

256
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:03,000
Supporting the work of world evangelism,

257
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:06,000
both prayerfully as well as financially,

258
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:09,000
through our local church is one of the clearest,

259
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:12,000
and may I say most scriptural ways

260
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:19,000
to obey Christ's command to reach the world with the gospel.

261
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:22,000
And by the way, can I take yet one more opportunity tonight

262
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:26,000
to remind you that reaching the world with the gospel,

263
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:29,000
it isn't a suggestion to be ignored.

264
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:32,000
It is a command to be obeyed.

265
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:36,000
And Jesus said in the gospel of John chapter 14 and verse 15,

266
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:40,000
if you love me, do you remember what he said?

267
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:43,000
Do much more than just sing, oh, how I love Jesus,

268
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:47,000
because quite honestly, talk is really cheap.

269
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:53,000
Jesus said, if you love me, keep my commandments.

270
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:57,000
Shortly before Jesus ascended back to his throne in glory,

271
00:14:57,000 --> 00:15:00,000
Jesus told his disciple in the book of Acts,

272
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:04,000
but ye shall receive power after that the Holy Ghost

273
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:09,000
is come upon you, and ye shall be witnesses unto me.

274
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:12,000
Somebody that knows the Bible, tell me that next word.

275
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:15,000
Both, that's right, both.

276
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:17,000
Do you know what that word both means?

277
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:21,000
It means simultaneously at the same time.

278
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:26,000
Both, Jesus said, here's where I want you to be witnesses.

279
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:29,000
Let's start in Jerusalem.

280
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:32,000
And then I want you to branch out and go from Jerusalem

281
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:35,000
and in Samaria and into all Judea,

282
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:38,000
and ultimately unto where?

283
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:41,000
The Bible says the uttermost parts of the earth.

284
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:48,000
So if Christ commands us to be witnesses for him,

285
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:53,000
both in Jerusalem and in all Judea and in Samaria

286
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:56,000
and under the uttermost part, how in the world

287
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:59,000
did Jesus ask something of us

288
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:02,000
that we do not possess within our power to do?

289
00:16:02,000 --> 00:16:05,000
How can we be in Oakton, Virginia,

290
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:10,000
and yet be in Uruguay at the same time?

291
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:14,000
We do it through partnerships that have been formed

292
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:20,000
through the missions outreach of our local Bible-believing church.

293
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:23,000
And therefore, since that is most definitely the case,

294
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:27,000
I'm going to encourage you to consider just a few truths

295
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:30,000
directly from the text.

296
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:34,000
Truths concerning our treasures.

297
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:37,000
Quickly, number one tonight.

298
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:42,000
Jesus calls our attention to the perishing nature

299
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:45,000
of earthly treasures.

300
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:49,000
Isn't it interesting that according to verse 19,

301
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:53,000
the Lord begins the verse with a very solemn

302
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:57,000
and may I say a very sobering warning.

303
00:16:57,000 --> 00:16:59,000
Jesus says,

304
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:05,000
lay not up for yourselves treasures upon earth.

305
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:08,000
Now again, please do not misunderstand.

306
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:10,000
Earthly treasures in and of themselves,

307
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:12,000
they're not sinful.

308
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:17,000
But the Bible clearly teaches that they at their best,

309
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:21,000
they're unstable, they are temporary,

310
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:25,000
and they are certainly unsatisfying.

311
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:29,000
In fact, the Lord drives that point home here in the text

312
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:34,000
by naming three enemies of material wealth.

313
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:39,000
Do you see the three enemies of material wealth in the text?

314
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:42,000
The Bible speaks of the moth.

315
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:45,000
The Bible speaks of rust.

316
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:49,000
And then the Bible speaks of thieves.

317
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:52,000
Each one of these enemies of material wealth

318
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:57,000
reminds us that everything you and I see today,

319
00:17:57,000 --> 00:17:59,000
everything we can touch today,

320
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:07,000
is subject to decay, to loss, and removal.

321
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:13,000
The moth, the rust, and the thieves.

322
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:19,000
First of all, the moth speaks of silent destruction.

323
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:22,000
And I say that because in Matthew's day,

324
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:28,000
wealth was often measured by the amount of fine garments people owned.

325
00:18:28,000 --> 00:18:32,000
However, as fine as a garment could have possibly been made,

326
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:34,000
moths, are you listening?

327
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:39,000
Moths could and often would destroy such garments

328
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:46,000
slowly but ever so surely from within.

329
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:55,000
That's why I say the image here emphasizes a gradual unseen decay.

330
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:59,000
The moth speaks of silent destruction.

331
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:04,000
The rust speaks of slow corrosion.

332
00:19:04,000 --> 00:19:08,000
In fact, I found it interesting while studying for the message tonight

333
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:11,000
that the Greek word translated rust in the text

334
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:17,000
literally means, listen, eating or consumption.

335
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:22,000
It includes corrosion, but it also speaks of spoilage

336
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:29,000
as grain rotting in barns as much as metal oxidizing.

337
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:33,000
This is a Bible truth that assures us, are you listening?

338
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:42,000
Every carefully stored resource is subject to the natural process of decay.

339
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:46,000
What man preserves, time consumes.

340
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:51,000
And therefore we gather from the text that creation itself

341
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:55,000
works against the permanence of earthly wealth.

342
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:59,000
The rust speaks of slow corrosion.

343
00:19:59,000 --> 00:20:01,500
No corrosion.

344
00:20:01,500 --> 00:20:06,139
And then the thieves speak of sudden loss.

345
00:20:06,139 --> 00:20:11,979
Unlike moth and rust, thieves involve sudden loss.

346
00:20:11,979 --> 00:20:14,819
Eternal loss.

347
00:20:14,819 --> 00:20:17,079
Again, it's interesting, in Matthew's day,

348
00:20:17,079 --> 00:20:20,360
homes were often made of clay or mud brick.

349
00:20:20,360 --> 00:20:25,500
And therefore, they were very easily broken through by digging.

350
00:20:25,500 --> 00:20:27,500
And therefore, it goes without saying,

351
00:20:27,500 --> 00:20:31,299
death could vanish in a moment due to crime

352
00:20:31,299 --> 00:20:34,299
or economic collapse.

353
00:20:34,299 --> 00:20:42,139
What took years to accumulate could be gone.

354
00:20:42,139 --> 00:20:44,540
Just like that.

355
00:20:44,540 --> 00:20:48,380
It's no wonder the Bible says in Proverbs chapter 23

356
00:20:48,380 --> 00:20:49,580
and verse 5,

357
00:20:49,580 --> 00:20:54,659
Wilt thou set thine eyes upon that which is not?

358
00:20:54,659 --> 00:21:01,060
For riches certainly make themselves wings.

359
00:21:01,060 --> 00:21:04,660
They fly away as an eagle toward heaven.

360
00:21:04,660 --> 00:21:06,000
Isn't that interesting?

361
00:21:06,000 --> 00:21:09,000
Not as a blue bird towards heaven.

362
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:12,339
Not as a black bird towards heaven.

363
00:21:12,339 --> 00:21:15,639
But riches, they make themselves wings

364
00:21:15,639 --> 00:21:20,019
and they fly away as one of the strongest birds of all.

365
00:21:20,019 --> 00:21:21,620
Just like that.

366
00:21:21,620 --> 00:21:23,879
As an eagle toward heaven.

367
00:21:23,900 --> 00:21:26,279
That's exactly why in Proverbs chapter 11,

368
00:21:26,279 --> 00:21:28,739
the first portion of verse 28 says,

369
00:21:28,739 --> 00:21:33,580
He that trusteth in his riches shall fail.

370
00:21:33,580 --> 00:21:39,080
Not might fall, not might fail, but shall fall.

371
00:21:39,080 --> 00:21:40,559
Please hear me tonight.

372
00:21:40,559 --> 00:21:43,220
Whether gradual or immediate,

373
00:21:43,220 --> 00:21:47,099
earthly treasure never belongs to us.

374
00:21:47,099 --> 00:21:49,760
No matter how carefully it is guarded.

375
00:21:49,760 --> 00:21:52,459
No matter how carefully it is stored.

376
00:21:52,480 --> 00:21:54,980
No matter how carefully it is kept.

377
00:21:54,980 --> 00:21:57,220
It cannot, are you listening?

378
00:21:57,220 --> 00:22:00,120
It cannot be secured forever.

379
00:22:00,120 --> 00:22:04,559
The very moment we breathe our last breath on this earth,

380
00:22:04,559 --> 00:22:07,160
every possession will be left behind.

381
00:22:07,160 --> 00:22:09,399
I want you to listen to the preacher tonight.

382
00:22:09,399 --> 00:22:13,539
Not one title, not one dollar, not one cent,

383
00:22:13,539 --> 00:22:19,479
not one account will cross the threshold of eternity.

384
00:22:19,500 --> 00:22:22,740
That is exactly why the Bible says in the 49th Psalm,

385
00:22:22,740 --> 00:22:25,940
be not afraid when one is made rich,

386
00:22:25,940 --> 00:22:28,779
when the glory of his house is increased.

387
00:22:28,779 --> 00:22:33,440
For when he dieth, he shall carry nothing away.

388
00:22:33,440 --> 00:22:37,580
His glory shall not descend after him.

389
00:22:37,580 --> 00:22:39,220
Please hear me tonight.

390
00:22:39,220 --> 00:22:42,720
Earthly treasure always, it always comes

391
00:22:42,720 --> 00:22:45,000
with three guarantees.

392
00:22:45,000 --> 00:22:48,800
Decay, damage, and disappearance.

393
00:22:49,020 --> 00:22:51,179
According to the Bible, the world's wealth

394
00:22:51,179 --> 00:22:53,259
has an expiration date.

395
00:22:53,259 --> 00:22:57,059
And the world's wealth's expiration date

396
00:22:57,059 --> 00:23:02,059
has been stamped with moths and rust and thieves.

397
00:23:04,300 --> 00:23:06,899
Moths attack luxury.

398
00:23:06,899 --> 00:23:09,380
Rust attacks utility.

399
00:23:09,380 --> 00:23:12,139
Thieves attack security.

400
00:23:12,139 --> 00:23:15,679
Nothing, nothing, nothing on this earth,

401
00:23:15,679 --> 00:23:16,679
are you listening?

402
00:23:16,699 --> 00:23:21,000
Nothing will escape loss, no matter how large the account,

403
00:23:21,000 --> 00:23:23,000
no matter how vast the possessions.

404
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:24,199
Let me say it again.

405
00:23:24,199 --> 00:23:28,080
Nothing on this earth will escape loss.

406
00:23:28,080 --> 00:23:32,279
Ecclesiastes chapter five teaches us in verse 15

407
00:23:32,279 --> 00:23:36,580
that we came into this world naked from our mother's wombs

408
00:23:36,580 --> 00:23:39,759
and we're leaving the same way.

409
00:23:41,559 --> 00:23:44,960
It was just a few weeks ago now that Cassie's mama

410
00:23:45,880 --> 00:23:47,559
went home to be with the Lord.

411
00:23:48,960 --> 00:23:52,800
Cassie was blessed to be in the room with her mother

412
00:23:52,800 --> 00:23:55,360
when she breathed her last breath.

413
00:23:56,639 --> 00:23:58,399
And when she breathed her last,

414
00:23:58,399 --> 00:24:02,399
she did not take her house with her.

415
00:24:02,399 --> 00:24:05,960
She did not take her land with her.

416
00:24:05,960 --> 00:24:09,039
She left every bank, are you listening?

417
00:24:10,360 --> 00:24:13,119
She left every bank account.

418
00:24:13,119 --> 00:24:17,600
She left every dress, she left every automobile,

419
00:24:17,600 --> 00:24:20,239
are you listening this evening?

420
00:24:20,239 --> 00:24:25,239
The perishing nature of earthly treasures.

421
00:24:27,040 --> 00:24:29,640
In the same portion of the Bible,

422
00:24:29,640 --> 00:24:33,119
Jesus not only addressed the perishing nature

423
00:24:33,119 --> 00:24:37,000
of earthly treasures, but he also addressed,

424
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:42,000
secondly, the permanence of heavenly treasures.

425
00:24:42,799 --> 00:24:45,600
Isn't it interesting while Matthew chapter six

426
00:24:45,600 --> 00:24:50,040
in verse 19 warns us what not to do,

427
00:24:50,040 --> 00:24:54,440
the following verse, Matthew chapter six in verse 20

428
00:24:54,440 --> 00:24:55,920
reveals what we should do.

429
00:24:57,440 --> 00:25:01,679
Notice the word starts with a little three letter conjunction

430
00:25:01,679 --> 00:25:06,679
but in light of the perishing nature of earthly treasures.

431
00:25:06,959 --> 00:25:10,760
But what does our Lord instruct us to do?

432
00:25:10,760 --> 00:25:13,480
Lay up for yourselves treasures in heaven

433
00:25:15,000 --> 00:25:19,040
where neither moth nor rust doth corrupt

434
00:25:19,040 --> 00:25:22,559
and where thieves do not break through nor steal.

435
00:25:23,640 --> 00:25:26,200
Here, ladies and gentlemen, in verse 20 of our text,

436
00:25:26,200 --> 00:25:30,720
we see the permanence of heavenly treasure.

437
00:25:30,720 --> 00:25:35,720
The permanence of heavenly treasure.

438
00:25:37,040 --> 00:25:39,959
As you pray about your investment in world evangelism

439
00:25:39,959 --> 00:25:43,119
in the coming year, isn't it interesting in the text

440
00:25:43,119 --> 00:25:47,040
that our Lord goes to great lengths to teach us

441
00:25:47,040 --> 00:25:51,399
about the permanence of heavenly treasures.

442
00:25:51,399 --> 00:25:54,320
And while doing so, he makes it abundantly clear

443
00:25:54,320 --> 00:25:57,880
that unlike our earthly treasure,

444
00:25:57,880 --> 00:26:02,600
heavenly treasures are never subject to decay.

445
00:26:03,880 --> 00:26:06,720
They are never subject to theft.

446
00:26:06,720 --> 00:26:09,880
No, the Bible teaches in our text

447
00:26:10,679 --> 00:26:14,679
that our heavenly treasures are guarded by God himself.

448
00:26:14,679 --> 00:26:17,399
You see, Christian friend, heaven's economy

449
00:26:17,399 --> 00:26:21,720
is never affected by inflation, recession, or loss.

450
00:26:21,720 --> 00:26:24,480
Heavenly treasures are accumulated

451
00:26:24,480 --> 00:26:28,359
when eternal work is accomplished for God's glory.

452
00:26:28,359 --> 00:26:31,440
Heavenly treasures are accumulated

453
00:26:31,440 --> 00:26:34,959
as the gospel is preached, as sinners are saved,

454
00:26:34,959 --> 00:26:39,279
as churches are planted, as disciples are made.

455
00:26:39,279 --> 00:26:42,239
Please hear me tonight, fellowship Baptist Church.

456
00:26:42,239 --> 00:26:45,799
Every missionary sent, every Bible distributed,

457
00:26:45,799 --> 00:26:48,720
every church planted, every soul won

458
00:26:48,720 --> 00:26:52,320
represents an eternal return in heaven

459
00:26:52,320 --> 00:26:57,320
as a result of a temporary investment on this earth.

460
00:26:58,440 --> 00:27:02,640
That's why I say when you invest in world evangelism

461
00:27:02,640 --> 00:27:05,839
every single month, every single week,

462
00:27:05,839 --> 00:27:08,079
however the Lord leads you to do it,

463
00:27:08,119 --> 00:27:10,239
you are making an investment

464
00:27:10,239 --> 00:27:14,160
in which you cannot and will not lose.

465
00:27:16,519 --> 00:27:18,000
I'll tell you what I want you to do.

466
00:27:18,000 --> 00:27:20,359
You were blessed, most of you,

467
00:27:20,359 --> 00:27:23,279
were blessed to be here Monday night.

468
00:27:23,279 --> 00:27:26,399
And I preached out of the book of Philippians chapter four

469
00:27:26,399 --> 00:27:28,920
on the thought, the opportunity

470
00:27:28,920 --> 00:27:31,640
that was not missed in missions.

471
00:27:31,640 --> 00:27:34,160
I want you, before I give you my last point,

472
00:27:34,160 --> 00:27:36,320
I want you to turn with me, if you would please,

473
00:27:36,359 --> 00:27:38,839
to Philippians chapter four once again.

474
00:27:38,839 --> 00:27:40,760
Philippians chapter four.

475
00:27:41,640 --> 00:27:45,200
Do you remember what Paul said to his friends at Philippi

476
00:27:45,200 --> 00:27:49,920
according to Philippians chapter four and verse 17?

477
00:27:49,920 --> 00:27:53,720
Paul commended them in chapter four

478
00:27:53,720 --> 00:27:57,760
for their partnership with him in his missions endeavors.

479
00:27:57,760 --> 00:28:02,000
In fact, Paul said in verse 15 of that chapter,

480
00:28:02,000 --> 00:28:03,720
now you Philippians know also

481
00:28:03,720 --> 00:28:05,480
that in the beginning of the gospel

482
00:28:05,480 --> 00:28:07,640
when I departed from Macedonia,

483
00:28:07,640 --> 00:28:09,519
no church communicated with me

484
00:28:09,519 --> 00:28:12,760
as concerning giving and receiving, but ye only.

485
00:28:12,760 --> 00:28:14,399
For even in Thessalonica,

486
00:28:14,399 --> 00:28:16,959
you sent once again unto my necessity,

487
00:28:16,959 --> 00:28:19,040
verse 17, don't miss it,

488
00:28:19,040 --> 00:28:21,480
not because I desire a gift,

489
00:28:21,480 --> 00:28:26,480
but I desire fruit that may abound to your account.

490
00:28:27,679 --> 00:28:29,320
Isn't this interesting?

491
00:28:30,320 --> 00:28:35,320
Paul, listen, Paul uses a commercial terminology

492
00:28:35,679 --> 00:28:38,960
used in Roman commerce

493
00:28:38,960 --> 00:28:41,200
that every single one of those Philippians

494
00:28:41,200 --> 00:28:43,080
would have been familiar with.

495
00:28:44,119 --> 00:28:46,599
Paul reminds them here in the text

496
00:28:46,599 --> 00:28:48,679
that they had an account with God.

497
00:28:48,679 --> 00:28:49,760
Are you listening?

498
00:28:50,679 --> 00:28:53,479
He reminds them they had an account with God.

499
00:28:53,479 --> 00:28:58,479
According to the text, it was a very personal account.

500
00:28:59,200 --> 00:29:01,599
Notice the Holy Ghost of God

501
00:29:01,599 --> 00:29:06,559
led Paul to use the words your account in the text.

502
00:29:06,559 --> 00:29:11,559
And then the Holy Ghost through the pen of the apostle Paul

503
00:29:12,080 --> 00:29:17,080
begins to go into very great detail

504
00:29:17,280 --> 00:29:22,280
concerning the Philippian believers account with God.

505
00:29:25,200 --> 00:29:26,599
First of all, the Bible speaks

506
00:29:26,599 --> 00:29:29,119
of the principle of their account.

507
00:29:29,119 --> 00:29:34,119
Again, the words your account imply divine bookkeeping.

508
00:29:34,840 --> 00:29:36,359
And the fact, listen,

509
00:29:36,359 --> 00:29:41,359
the fact that God keeps really good records,

510
00:29:42,880 --> 00:29:45,039
really good records.

511
00:29:45,039 --> 00:29:47,159
Can I just say this about our God?

512
00:29:48,200 --> 00:29:52,760
Our God's pencil doesn't have an eraser on it.

513
00:29:53,919 --> 00:29:54,760
You know why?

514
00:29:54,760 --> 00:29:56,320
God never messes up.

515
00:29:56,320 --> 00:29:58,320
Especially.

516
00:29:58,320 --> 00:30:05,320
when it comes to accounting, God keeps really good records.

517
00:30:05,320 --> 00:30:12,320
Nothing invested in the gospel goes unnoticed or unrewarded.

518
00:30:12,320 --> 00:30:14,320
The principle of their account.

519
00:30:14,320 --> 00:30:17,320
The Bible teaches us about the product of their account.

520
00:30:17,320 --> 00:30:19,320
Oh, don't miss this.

521
00:30:19,320 --> 00:30:25,320
Notice that Paul never emphasizes the size of the offerings

522
00:30:25,320 --> 00:30:32,320
the Philippians sent, but rather the spiritual outcome of them.

523
00:30:32,320 --> 00:30:38,320
